To create a Custom Audience in Facebook Ads (inside Meta Ads Manager), follow these steps:

1. Open Ads Manager

Go to

2. Open Audiences
Click the Menu (☰) in the top-left.
Under Advertise, select Audiences.
3. Click “Create Audience”

Choose Custom Audience.

4. Select Audience Source

You’ll see different sources:

✅ Website Traffic
People who visited your website.
(Requires Meta Pixel installed)

Examples:

All website visitors
People who visited specific pages
People who spent more time on your site

✅ Customer List
Upload:

Email list
Phone numbers
Customer names

Format: CSV / TXT

✅ Engagement
People who interacted with your:

Facebook Page
Instagram account
Videos
Lead forms
Events

Examples:

People who liked/commented/shared your post
People who watched 50% of your video
People who messaged your page

✅ App Activity
People who used your mobile app.

✅ Offline Activity
People who visited your physical store or took action offline.

5. Set Rules

Example for website:

URL contains /checkout
Last 30 days visitors only

Example for engagement:

People who engaged with your page in last 365 days
6. Name Your Audience

Example:

Website Visitors 30 Days
IG Engagers 90 Days
Video Viewers 50%
7. Click Create Audience

Facebook will start collecting or matching people.

Bonus Tip:

After creating Custom Audience, create a Lookalike Audience from it to find similar people.

Example:
Custom Audience → Purchasers → Lookalike 1% USA

Custom Audience helps in:
✔ Retargeting visitors
✔ Re-engaging old customers
✔ Lower ad cost
✔ Better conversion rate


